      <profileDesc>
         <abstract><p>Composed for — or perhaps by — the Italian Catholic missionary <persName ref="PRS9683Urbino">Giusto da Urbino (1814–1856)</persName>, who called himself “ʾAbbā Yosṭos” in Gəʿəz. He sent the only known copy, part of an assembly of loose paper gatherings, to Antoine d’Abbadie prior to his death.</p></abstract>
